Cell["Summary", "Section"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "This is a simple exercise in tensor manipulation using ",
 StyleBox["xAct",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " and ",
 StyleBox["xPrint",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ".\nWe will obtain the geodesic deviation equation as described in \nWald : \
General Relativity pag 46-47 leading to eq. 3.3 .18\nWald uses ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["T", TraditionalForm]]],
 " for the tangent vector to a geodesic flow, we use ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["u", TraditionalForm]]],
 " as in MTW\[CloseCurlyQuote]s \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]Gravitation\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote].\nWald uses ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["X", TraditionalForm]]],
 " for the separation vector, we use ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["n", TraditionalForm]]],
 " as in MTW\[CloseCurlyQuote]s \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]Gravitation\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]."
}], "Text"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "We shall follow Wald and assume that we know what the Riemann tensor is (we \
know it arises in the commutation of covariant derivatives).\nWe will use ",
 StyleBox["xAct",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " to see what is the relationship between the Riemann tensor and the \
acceleration of the separation vector of a geodesic flow."
}], "Text"]
}, Closed]],

